<span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> - *Sozialdemokratische Partei Deutschlands* (Social Democratic Party of Germany) - this is us. We are a socialist and democratic party of the working class. We are the heirs of the legacy of Marx and Engels, Lassalle and Bebel. We are the foremost defenders of the Republic. The modern <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> was formed from a merger of the "Majority" <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, which supported the Great War, and the "Independent" <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> or <span style="color: #D47B9B;">**USPD**</span>, which opposed the war.

<span style="color: #000000;">**Z**</span> - *Zentrumspartei* (Center Party) - a centrist to center-right Catholic party that supports the Republic, and has historically supported many of our labor, welfare, and anti-militarist priorities. They have often been in coalitions with us. They are often associated with the <span style="color: #A2D8E0;">**BVP**</span> (Bavarian People's Party), which represents Catholics in <span style="color: #00CCFF;">Bavaria</span>. [? if (year >= 1930 or chancellor == "Brüning") and z_leader == "Kaas": They have appeared to take a more conservative turn recently, with the rise of Brüning and the party leader, Ludwig Kaas. ?][? if (year >= 1930 or chancellor == "Brüning") and z_leader == "Stegerwald": They have appeared to take a more conservative turn recently, with the rise of Brüning and the party leader, Adam Stegerwald, who has taken a focus on interconfessionalizing the party. ?][? if (year >= 1930 or chancellor == "Brüning") and z_leader == "Joos": They have appeared to take a more conservative turn recently, with the rise of Brüning and support of austerity. ?][? if year >= 1930 and z_leader == "Kaiser": They have appeared to take a more leftist turn recently, with the election of Jakob Kaiser and support of certain left-wing economic policies. ?]

Current relations: [+ z_relation : relationships +]

[? if not lvp_formed: <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> - [? if ddp_name == "DDP": *Deutsche Demokratische Partei* (German Democratic Party)?][? if ddp_name == "DStP": *Deutsche Staatspartei* (German State Party)?] - [? if ddp_name == "DDP": a left-liberal party, popular among the intelligentsia and educated middle class. Although, they have been shifting towards the right over the years. They have often been in coalitions with us. ?][? if ddp_name == "DStP": a liberal party, waning in popularity among the intelligentsia and middle class. [? if dstp_collapsed == 0: They have shifted considerably to the right in recent years and have merged with the political wing of the mildly antisemitic Young German Order in an effort to revive their party.?][? if dstp_collapsed == 1: They have shifted considerably to the right in recent years and have merged with the political wing of the mildly antisemitic Young German Order in an effort to revive their party. Furthermore, the Young German Order has broken off, essentially just leaving the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**DDP**</span> with a different name.?] They have often been in coalitions with us. ?] ?]

[? if not lvp_formed: Current relations: [+ ddp_relation : relationships +] ?]

[? if not lvp_formed: <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> - *Deutsche Volkspartei* (German People's Party) - a conservative-liberal party founded by Gustav Stresemann, supported by the middle classes, bourgeoisie and industrialists. The industrial and right wing of the party has been gaining noticeable influence in recent years with Stresemann's neglect of party affairs. [? if dvp_ideology == "Right": The industrial wing of the party has succeeded in it's takeover of the party and are much less inclined to work with us.?] We have occasionally been in coalitions. ?]

[? if not lvp_formed: Current relations: [+ dvp_relation : relationships +] ?]

[? if lvp_formed: <span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span> - *Liberale Volkspartei* (Liberal People's Party) - a liberal party, popular among the bourgeois and the middle class. Formed from a merger of the two former liberal parties, the left-liberal <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> and conservative-liberal <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>. Its predecessors have often been in coalitions with us. ?]

[? if lvp_formed: Current relations: [+ lvp_relation : relationships +] ?]

[? if kvp_formed: <span style="color: #0087DC;">**KVP**</span> - *Konservative Volkspartei* (Conservative People's Party) - a moderate right-wing conservative nationalist party, supported by rural workers, former aristocracy, landowners and conservative Lutherans. The party seeks to emulate the <span style="color: #0087DC;">Tory</span> conservatives in <span style="color: #C8102E;">Great Britain</span>. ?]

[? if kvp_formed: Current relations: [+ kvp_relation : relationships +] ?]

<span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> - *Deutschnationale Volkspartei* (German National People's Party) - a right-wing nationalist-conservative party, with authoritarian, monarchist, and racist elements. It is supported by the former aristocracy, rural landowners, and conservative Lutherans.

Current relations: [+ dnvp_relation : relationships +]

[? if dnf_formed: <span style="color: #003755;">**DNF**</span> - *Deutschnationale Front* (German National Front) - a far-right nationalist-conservative party, led by Alfred Hugenberg, originally split from the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>. It is supported by a small but loyal base of Hugenberg supporters, consisting of former aristocrats, racists and nationalists. ?]

[? if dnf_formed: Current relations: [+ dnf_relation : relationships +] ?]

<span style="color: #700000;">**KPD**</span> - *Kommunistische Partei Deutschlands* (German Communist Party) - a radical left-wing offshoot of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> that emerged in the aftermath of the German Revolution of 1918, they follow the path of Moscow, opposing parliamentary democracy in favor of a <span style="color: #750e0e;">Soviet</span>-style revolution.

Current relations: [+ kpd_relation : relationships +]

[? if sapd_formed: <span style="color: #9B0000;">**SAPD**</span> - Sozialistische Arbeiterpartei Deutschlands (Socialist Worker's Party of Germany) - a party recently formed in a split from the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, the <span style="color: #9B0000;">**SAPD**</span> is essentially an agglomeration of various left-wing splinter groups between the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> and <span style="color: #700000;">**KPD**</span>. ?]

<span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> - *Nationalsozialistische Deutsche Arbeiterpartei* - (National Socialist German Worker's Party, or <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span>) - a far-right nationalist and antisemitic party. Led by Adolf Hitler, they attempted a coup in 1923, and were banned for it, but have since been legalized.

Current relations: [+ nsdap_relation : relationships +]

